  "commentary": "**Dealer Hedging Commentary:**\n\nWith SPX at 6861.79 trading above the GEX flip at 6842, dealers are positioned long gamma and will mechanically sell rallies into the massive 6900 strike (+6918.1M GEX wall) while buying any dips back toward 6850-6860 support cluster. The thick positive gamma profile from 6850-7000 creates a strong mean-reverting environment where dealers provide natural stabilization through contrarian hedging flows. Key inflection points are the 6842 flip level below (where dealer behavior reverses) and the 6900 resistance wall above where selling pressure intensifies.\n\n**Bottom line:** Expect price to get pinned between 6850-6900 with dealers capping moves in both directions.",
